verses.roman:
bhaktera guṇa kahite prabhura bāḍaye ullāsa
bhakta-gaṇa-śreṣṭha tāte śrī-haridāsa

synonyms: bhaktera—of the devotees; guṇa—qualities; kahite—speaking; prabhura—of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; bāḍaye—increases; ullāsa—jubilation; bhakta-gaṇa—of all devotees; śreṣṭha—topmost; tāte—in that; śrī-haridāsa—Haridāsa Ṭhākura.
translation: Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu derives great pleasure from glorifying His devotees, and among the devotees, Haridāsa Ṭhākura is the foremost.
